org.activebpel.rt.bpel.server.engine
Class AePersistentProcessManager

java.lang.Object
  org.activebpel.rt.bpel.impl.AeManagerAdapter
      org.activebpel.rt.bpel.impl.AeAbstractProcessManager
          org.activebpel.rt.bpel.server.engine.AePersistentProcessManager
All Implemented Interfaces:
IAeManager, IAePersistentProcessManager, IAeProcessManager, IAeProcessWrapperMapCallback, IAeRecoverableProcessManager
public class AePersistentProcessManager
extends AeAbstractProcessManager
implements IAePersistentProcessManager, IAeProcessWrapperMapCallback, IAeRecoverableProcessManager

Implements process manager that persists processes to an instance of IAeStorage. This implementation counts references to process instances to decide when to persist a process to storage. This means that every call to createBusinessProcess(IAeProcessPlan) or getProcess(long) must must be balanced by a corresponding call to releaseProcess(IAeBusinessProcess).

getCurrentProcessWrapper

protected AeProcessWrapper getCurrentProcessWrapper(long aProcessId)
Returns the current process wrapper for the given process id or null if there is no process wrapper for the given process id. Does not increment the wrapper's reference count or acquire the process mutex the way getProcessWrapperWithMutex(long) does, so does not require a matching call to releaseProcessWrapperWithMutex(AeProcessWrapper). However, this means that successive calls to getCurrentProcessWrapper(long) with the same process id may return different process wrappers.

Parameters:
aProcessId -

getProcessNoUpdate

public IAeBusinessProcess getProcessNoUpdate(long aProcessId)
                                      throws AeBusinessProcessException
Description copied from interface: IAeProcessManager
Returns the business process with the specified process id, locking the process into memory. Each call to IAeProcessManager.getProcessNoUpdate(long) must be followed eventually by a matching call to IAeProcessManager.releaseProcess(IAeBusinessProcess). Calling IAeProcessManager.getProcessNoUpdate(long) instead of IAeProcessManager.getProcess(long) asserts that the caller will not modify the process, so that the process manager may discard the process from memory after it is released without updating its persistent representation (if there is one).

Specified by:

protected AeProcessWrapper getProcessWrapperWithMutex()
Returns process wrapper for the a temporary process id to ensure that we have room for this process in memory. The real Id is set afterwards. Each call to getProcessWrapperWithMutex(long) or getProcessWrapperWithMutex(long) must be followed eventually by a matching call to releaseProcessWrapperWithMutex(AeProcessWrapper).

getReleaseLagMillis

protected long getReleaseLagMillis(AeProcessWrapper aWrapper)
Called by releaseProcess(IAeBusinessProcess); returns the number of milliseconds to wait after the process goes quiescent before releasing the process from memory. This implementation returns either 0 (to release the process immediately) or the value from the engine configuration; subclasses should override this method to tailor the behavior.
